        "README.md": "# Remotion Skill\n\nAn AI skill for programmatic video generation using [Remotion](https://www.remotion.dev/) - a framework for creating videos with React.\n\n[![npm](https://img.shields.io/npm/v/remotion-skill-cli?style=flat-square&logo=npm&label=CLI)](https://www.npmjs.com/package/remotion-skill-cli)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/mquhuy/remotion-skill?style=flat-square&color=green)](LICENSE)\n\n## Features\n\n- **Forbidden patterns** - Teaches AI to avoid CSS transitions, Tailwind animate-*, and other patterns that break renders\n- **Frame-based animation** - Create videos using React components with precise frame control\n- **Interpolation & Springs** - Smooth animations using `interpolate()` and `spring()` functions\n- **Sequences & Series** - Compose complex video timelines with `<Sequence>` and `<Series>`\n- **Media support** - Embed video, audio, and images with `<Video>`, `<Audio>`, `<Img>`\n- **Programmatic rendering** - Render videos via CLI or Node.js scripts (batch, parallel)\n- **Web embedding** - Embed videos in web apps with `@remotion/player`\n- **AI verification workflow** - Mandatory render-and-fix loop before reporting success\n\n## Supported AI Assistants\n\n| Assistant | Installation Path | Skill Type |\n|-----------|-------------------|------------|\n| Claude Code | `.claude/skills/remotion/` | Full Skill |\n| OpenCode | `.opencode/skills/remotion/` | Full Skill |\n| Cursor | `.cursor/commands/` | Workflow |\n| Windsurf | `.windsurf/workflows/` | Workflow |\n| GitHub Copilot | `.github/prompts/` | Prompt |\n\n## Installation\n\n### Using CLI (Recommended)\n\n```bash\n# Install CLI globally\nnpm install -g remotion-skill-cli\n\n# Go to your project\ncd /path/to/your/project\n\n# Standard install (links to Remotion's GitHub for technical rules)\nremotion-skill init --ai claude      # Claude Code\nremotion-skill init --ai opencode    # OpenCode\nremotion-skill init --ai cursor      # Cursor\nremotion-skill init --ai windsurf    # Windsurf\nremotion-skill init --ai copilot     # GitHub Copilot\nremotion-skill init --ai all         # All assistants\n\n# Deep install (includes Remotion's official rules locally)\nremotion-skill init --ai claude --deep\n```\n\n### Install Modes\n\n| Mode | Command | What's Included |\n|------|---------|-----------------|\n| **Standard** | `--ai claude` | Our skill + links to Remotion's GitHub |\n| **Deep** | `--ai claude --deep` | Our skill + Remotion's rules downloaded locally |\n\n**Standard** is best for most users - always up-to-date with Remotion's latest docs.\n\n**Deep** is best for offline development or air-gapped environments.\n\n### Using Claude Marketplace (Claude Code)\n\nInstall directly in Claude Code with two commands:\n\n```\n/plugin marketplace add mquhuy/remotion-skill\n/plugin install remotion@remotion-skill\n```\n\n### Using npx (No Installation)\n\n```bash\n# Run directly without installing\ncd /path/to/your/project\nnpx remotion-skill-cli init --ai claude\n```\n\n### Manual Installation\n\nCopy the appropriate folder to your project:\n\n**For Claude Code:**\n```bash\nmkdir -p .claude/skills/remotion\ncurl -o .claude/skills/remotion/SKILL.md https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mquhuy/remotion-skill/main/.claude/skills/remotion/SKILL.md\n```\n\n**For OpenCode:**\n```bash\nmkdir -p .opencode/skills/remotion\ncurl -o .opencode/skills/remotion/SKILL.md https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mquhuy/remotion-skill/main/.opencode/skills/remotion/SKILL.md\n```\n\n**For Cursor:**\n```bash\nmkdir -p .cursor/commands\ncurl -o .cursor/commands/remotion.md https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mquhuy/remotion-skill/main/.cursor/commands/remotion.md\n```\n\n**For Windsurf:**\n```bash\nmkdir -p .windsurf/workflows\ncurl -o .windsurf/workflows/remotion.md https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mquhuy/remotion-skill/main/.windsurf/workflows/remotion.md\n```\n\n**For GitHub Copilot:**\n```bash\nmkdir -p .github/prompts\ncurl -o .github/prompts/remotion.prompt.md https://raw.githubusercontent.com/mquhuy/remotion-skill/main/.github/prompts/remotion.prompt.md\n```\n\n## Example\n\nHere's a video generated using the Remotion skill with a single prompt:\n\n**Prompt:**\n> Render a video of two spaceships fighting on a 2D world. At the end, one of the drops down and dies\n\n**Result:**\n\n![Spaceship Battle](examples/spaceship-battle.gif)\n\n## Usage\n\nOnce installed, the skill activates automatically when you request video-related work:\n\n```\nCreate a video intro animation with my logo fading in\n\nGenerate a 10-second countdown video\n\nBuild a video that shows text sliding in from the left\n```\n\n### Trigger Keywords\n\nThe skill responds to:\n- \"create video\", \"generate video\", \"render video\"\n- \"remotion\", \"animation\", \"mp4\"\n- \"video component\", \"video composition\"\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nremotion-skill/\n├── src/remotion-skill/           # Source of truth\n│   └── SKILL.md\n├── cli/                          # CLI installer (remotion-skill-cli on npm)\n│   ├── src/\n│   │   ├── index.ts\n│   │   └── commands/init.ts\n│   ├── assets/                   # Bundled skill files\n│   └── package.json\n├── .claude/skills/remotion/      # Claude Code skill\n├── .opencode/skills/remotion/    # OpenCode skill\n├── .cursor/commands/             # Cursor workflow\n├── .windsurf/workflows/          # Windsurf workflow\n├── .github/prompts/              # GitHub Copilot prompt\n├── .claude-plugin/               # Claude Marketplace config\n├── .shared/remotion              # Symlink to source\n├── CLAUDE.md                     # Repo guidance\n├── LICENSE                       # MIT License\n└── README.md                     # This file\n```\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n### Essential Imports\n\n```tsx\nimport {\n  useCurrentFrame,\n  useVideoConfig,\n  AbsoluteFill,\n  Sequence,\n  Series,\n  interpolate,\n  spring,\n  interpolateColors,\n  Video,\n  Audio,\n  Img,\n  OffthreadVideo,\n  staticFile,\n  Composition,\n} from 'remotion';\n```\n\n### Basic Animation\n\n```tsx\nconst frame = useCurrentFrame();\nconst { fps } = useVideoConfig();\n\nconst opacity = interpolate(frame, [0, 30], [0, 1], {\n  extrapolateLeft: 'clamp',\n  extrapolateRight: 'clamp',\n});\n\nconst scale = spring({\n  frame,\n  fps,\n  config: { damping: 200, stiffness: 100, mass: 0.5 },\n});\n```\n\n### CLI Commands\n\n```bash\n# Start Remotion Studio (development)\nnpx remotion studio\n\n# Render video\nnpx remotion render src/index.ts CompositionId out/video.mp4\n\n# Render with props\nnpx remotion render src/index.ts CompositionId out/video.mp4 \\\n  --props='{\"titleText\":\"Hello World\"}'\n\n# Render still image\nnpx remotion still src/index.ts CompositionId out/thumbnail.png --frame=30\n```\n\n## AI Workflow\n\nWhen generating Remotion videos, AI assistants follow this mandatory workflow:\n\n1. **Generate** - Create video component following skill patterns\n2. **Register** - Add composition to `src/Root.tsx`\n3. **Verify** - Run render and fix ALL errors\n4. **Report** - Only notify user after successful render\n\n## License\n\nMIT License - see [LICENSE](LICENSE) for details.\n\n## Contributing\n\n1. Fork the repository\n2. Create a feature branch: `git checkout -b feat/amazing-feature`\n3. Commit changes: `git commit -m 'Add amazing feature'`\n4. Push to branch: `git push origin feat/amazing-feature`\n5. Open a Pull Request\n\n## Related\n\n- [Remotion Documentation](https://www.remotion.dev/docs/)\n- [Remotion GitHub](https://github.com/remotion-dev/remotion)\n- [Remotion Official Skill](https://github.com/remotion-dev/remotion/tree/main/packages/skills) - Technical rules we reference (with `--deep`, these are installed locally)\n- [UI/UX Pro Max Skill](https://github.com/nextlevelbuilder/ui-ux-pro-max-skill) - Inspiration for this skill structure\n"
